.TH "smk_access" 9 "smk_access" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
smk_access \- determine if a subject has a specific access to an object
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" smk_access
.BI "(struct smack_known *subject "  ","
.BI "struct smack_known *object "  ","
.BI "int request "  ","
.BI "struct smk_audit_info *a "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "subject" 12
a pointer to the subject's Smack label entry
.IP "object" 12
a pointer to the object's Smack label entry
.IP "request" 12
the access requested, in "MAY" format
.IP "a" 12
a pointer to the audit data
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function looks up the subject/object pair in the
access rule list and returns 0 if the access is permitted,
non zero otherwise.

Smack labels are shared on smack_list
